            <span class="utterance" who="#warsagerB" start="754.156" end="x">And to eat we received very little. And there had happened at that time in the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> a case that a pig was stolen from the pigsty, and for that the entire <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> had to fast. And for four days we received nothing to eat. And every day we had to stand from three till eleven in the evening. And many times it rained. And there were such cloudy days and so cold. And the people couldn't endure it. The people were dropping like flies, it was so bad.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="789.581" end="x">Weren't you working? How could they let you stand all day?</span>
